 Men of Ogun state police command have arrested one 30-year old Olawoyin Segun for having unlawful carnal knowledge of a 16-year old girl, name withheld. The arrest of the suspect followed a report by the victim, who reported at Ibafo police station that the suspect, who is a family friend, came to their house on the said date at about 1:30 pm asking for her parents. She stated further that having realized that her parents had gone to church, the suspect grabbed her and forcefully had carnal knowledge of her. According to her, in an attempt to rescue herself, she gave the suspect serious human bite, but he still had his way, hence she reported the case. Upon the report, the DPO Ibafo division, SP Abiodun Ayinde detailed his detectives to the scene at Mapara Makogi area of Ibafo, where the randy man was promptly arrested. On interrogation, the suspect , who confessed being a friend to the family of the victim, claimed not to have known what came over him that made him to do such thing to the girl, who always sees him as her brother. Meanwhile, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, PPRO, Ogun State Police Command said the state commissioner of police, CP Bashir Makama, has ordered the transfer of the suspect to anti-human trafficking and child labour unit of the state Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department for proper investigation and prosecution. 